RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 1 6F Turf CR: 85. Maiden Claiming Purse 35000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE, FOUR, AND FIVE YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $50,000. (Rail at 30 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DEVIL MOON dueled for the lead from outside, shook free from BOLT FROM HEAVEN in upper stretch, had the rider lose his whip at the eighth pole, then drew off under hand urging. BOLT FROM HEAVEN dueled inside DEVIL MOON, was coaxed along through the bend, could not kick on with the winner in upper stretch and stayed on to best the rest. SNAPP DADDY chased between rivals then jumped crossing onto the turn and got bumped while being put in tight quarters between rivals, chased three wide into the turn, moved out to travel four deep around the bend, kept on through the lane and outkicked CHARLIE'S GHOST for the show honors. CHARLIE'S GHOST stalked between rivals, got put in tight and had to check entering the turn, regained stride and split foes again on the turn, chased two wide into the lane and got edged for third. CHAO PHRAYA drifted out and bumped rival crossing the dirt, stalked along the inside leaving the backstretch, checked inside a pair of rivals into the turn, remained inside to the stretch and could not rally. MAFIA MAN broke a step slow, chased three deep into the turn, started to weaken late on the bend and faded. COACH OTT was off a bit slow, lagged behind early, moved to the inside, saved ground trailing into the lane and was never a factor.

ENTRY.NAME: Chao Phraya
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked inside, drifted/bumped xing, checked 3/8, no rally

ENTRY.NAME: Devil Moon
ENTRY.COMMENT: dueled outside, cleared, lost whip 1/8, drew off

RACE.FOOTNOTES: FLATTERWITHJEWELS raced up close to the outside of the leader early, drew alongside on the far turn to fight for the lead, took over past the quarter pole, shook free at the top of the lane and drew off. SHVERE ARBETER lost her footing briefly at the start but still came away with the others, established the front on the inside then was taken in hand on the first turn and early backstretch to control the pace, met the bid from FLATTERWITHJEWELS on the far turn, lost command late on the bend, could not keep up at the top of the stretch but kept on to hold the place. RENEGADE PRINCESS broke out a bit at the start, tracked three wide early, went two wide into the far turn, angled out around the bend, came five wide into the stretch and gained the show. ROMAN EMPRESS broke out but was quickly correctly, forwardly placed three deep early, was asked three then four wide chasing the top pair around the second bend and could not offer the needed response. SPLICER stalked in the two path early, saved ground while dropping out of range on the far turn and weakened in the lane.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: MY RANSOM stalked off the inside or outside a rival, went two then three wide around the bend, tipped out to launch a rally widest in the drive, surged late and got up in time. DEFENSOR FORTIS broke out and was quickly straightened, closest in pursuit of the leader from outside to the turn, chased two wide around the bend, drew alongside in upper stretch and headed EDDIE'S LAST with a furlong remaining, took over soon after, inched ahead with a sixteenth left to run and got nailed on the wire. BRONKO NAGURSKI broke inward, bobbled a bit crossing over the dirt, had to pause when the leader came over a bit early, chased along the inside then two wide into the lane, moved out but drifted back inward then had to alter in from behind EDDIE'S LAST at the sixteenth pole and finished willingly for a game third. EDDIE'S LAST took control early, set all the pace on the inside to the stretch, headed by DEFENSOR FORTIS at the eighth pole, relinquished the lead shortly after and yielded in the final sixteenth. COMMISSIONER H broke cleanly then dropped back, lost his action crossing back on to the turn, trailed next to the fence through the bend and was not a factor.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: GYPSY LYNN cleared and crossed over early, showed the way along the inside through the turn, asked left-handed in upper stretch and powered away. TENACIOUS LADY broke out and brushed rival, chased near then at the back outside a rival, went two then three wide around the bend, tipped out in the stretch and bested the rest. FRIED ASPARAGUS lost path early and moved back to last, inched closer from inside to the turn, saved ground around the bend, came off the rail a bit in the drive and was along for the show. STORM D'ORO got brushed from inside leaving the gate, stalked off the rail then got bumped from inside on the backstretch, was closest in pursuit two then three wide on the turn but flattened when called upon. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. (Non-Starters For A Claiming Price Of $40,000 Or Less In Their Last Starts Preferred). (Rail at 30 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: UNCLE JOHN dueled for the lead outside TOUCHDOWN KITTLE, carried a short lead into the stretch, battled through the final furlong gamely prevailed. TOUCHDOWN KITTLE dueled for command into and around the turn and into the stretch, battled down the lane but had to settle for second best. MAXVILLE was off slow and dropped back early, whittle the gap while trailing up the backstretch, passed rivals from outside around the turn and kept on for a clear third. INFINITEEXPERIENCE was up close outside the top pair then stalked three wide into the turn, chased two wide into the lane and weakened. SAN JAC raced greenly changing leads back and forth early on, dropped back around the turn and trailed into the stretch and weakened.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 6 1M Dirt CR: 96. Maiden Optional Claiming Purse 40000. RACE.FOOTNOTES: EVER A REBEL raced up close to the outside of the leader in the early going, headed rival on the far turn under light coaxing, given his cue with a quarter mile remaining, inched ahead under right and left handed urging, cleared approaching the sixteenth pole and remained strong to the line. LOOKS RARE went up to take control on the inside, received some pressure from EVER A REBEL in the middle stages, dueled with that rival through the far turn and lost command with at the quarter pole, stayed with the winner to midstretch then yielded and managed to save the place. RIVERSIDE bumped leaving the gate, tracked three wide early, angled in on the far turn, moved out in the stretch and went willingly late to miss the place. EXCEL CALCULATOR got pinballed at the start, trailed five then four wide early, advanced from outside up the backstretch to get into range, took the second turn three wide then tipped four wide into the stretch and flattened out. STONKS stalked two wide early, angled out on the far turn and failed to threaten. SAM MALONE shifted in bumped rival twice at the start, chased four wide on the clubhouse turn, three to four wide on the second bend and failed to menace. QUALITY CAT got crowded a bit between rivals at the start, tucked inside off the pace, saved ground to the stretch and came up empty.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: SELL THE DREAM stalked two wide early, moved inside on the backstretch, tipped out into the lane, then drew alongside the leader and took over in upper stretch, moved clear with a furlong remaining and held well under a drive. RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 8 1 1/16M Dirt CR: 80. Maiden Claiming Purse 22000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE, FOUR, AND FIVE YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DEEP RIVER stalked from inside, chased behind the leader through the far turn, lacked room exiting the bend, tipped out and bumped rival entering the stretch, split foes to gain command at the top of the stretch, quickly cleared and powered away under a drive. DONTTESTYOURLUCK settled inside, chased in range entering the far turn, angled four wide into the lane, launched a bid in upper stretch but was no match for the winner and stayed on to hold second. ICE STORM raced two wide near the back behind rivals then had to tip three wide on the first turn, found a some light traffic early on the backstretch, moved closer in the middle stages, went four wide into the far turn, got fanned six wide into the lane, kept on through the drive and got edged for the place honors. DANZ TILL TEN pulled along the inside and shifted to the two path into the first turn, continued to tug forward and went up to press the pace from outside, lost touch with the leader past the five-sixteenths pole, re-bid three deep while getting bumped at the top of the stretch, then weakened in the furlong grounds. SAMBA FLAVOR brushed at the start, chased three wide off the pace early, remained off the rail into the far turn, angled five wide leaving the bend and brushed with outer rival, remained close into the final furlong then flattened out. PARS AND BIRDIES chased three then four wide early, went three wide into the lane, altered out at the eight pole and failed to menace. NEVER SORRY was off slow to begin and trailed early, passed tired rivals and failed to make an impact. CHIEF COUNCIL brushed leaving the gate, cleared early and crossed over to the inside, gained company to the outside and set the pace under pressure in the middle stages, moved clear past the five-sixteenths pole, challenged again at the top of the lane, relinquished the lead and weakened in the final furlong. STREET MOGUL stalked three then two wide early, entered the second bend four wide, angled down to the inside and came up empty.
